        .col-md-8.col-12
            h1 John Lo - Founder
            p.lead.lh-180(style="font-size:20px;")

              | John is currently based in Cologne, Germany and was born and raised in Dallas, Texas. He was the first product engineer at the Andreessen Horowitz-led company Gigster. He studied statistics and computer science at Harvard University. John developed the initial Zerobase contact tracing method to give communities a scalable, privacy-first, virtual public health resource in the face of rapidly diminishing physical resources. His past projects have included tamper-proof hardware, zero knowledge proofs, and enabling public health administration for marginalized communities. Privacy and health have always been at the forefront of John’s interests.

